Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.0

Package: fixpart
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4.0), util-linux, coreutils, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ntfs-3g, exfat-fuse, exfatprogs
Description: Automatic partition repair tool for Linux
 FixPart is an intelligent bash script that automatically repairs
 corrupted partitions on Ubuntu/Linux systems. It supports multiple
 filesystem types including NTFS, EXT2/3/4, exFAT, and FAT32.
 .
 Features:
  - Automatic filesystem type detection
  - Intelligent repair based on partition type
  - Colorful and user-friendly interface
  - Automatic dependency installation
  - Safe unmounting before repair
  - Optional automatic mounting after repair
